  <body>
    <segment id="1" parent="18" relname="span">
I&apos;m pleased with the level of thinking going on here on the aspect of intuitiveness.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="20" relname="span"> 
Our discussion is definitely geared toward understanding that usability is not only common sense. </segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="4" relname="circumstance">
When we begin describing usability in terms of attributes -- intuitiveness, ease of use, learnability and others ---</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="19" relname="span"> we have to be able to link these to concrete measures. </segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="4" relname="otherwise">
Otherwise, common sense is our only fall back, which is entirely too vague. </segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="28" relname="span">

Comments have also been made in regard to user experience level and intuitiveness. </segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="27" relname="span">
This is key to do substantial testing on the novice level </segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="21" relname="span">
because so many variables exist in terms of technology experience. </segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="26" relname="span">
We cannot lump all users together and assume that one size fits all. </segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="25" relname="span">
This is the heart of why we do user testing -- </segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="12" relname="antithesis">
we design for many concepts concurrently (such as intuitiveness), </segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="24" relname="span">
but we must observe how this actually works (or not). </segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="23" relname="span">
Without the insight from users, we are drawing our own conclusions. </segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="22" relname="span">
(Most people in this class are highly skilled in technology. </segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="14" relname="elaboration">
It&apos;s natural for us to &quot;forget&quot; what being a novice user &quot;feels&quot; like. </segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="14" relname="elaboration">
We have to observe others to recall the difficulties.) </segment>
    <segment id="17" parent="18" relname="summary">

It makes me proud to see so many fine HCI advocates in this class!
</segment>
